<p>I'm using Xcode to build an external source code (not originally written for OS X). On has an include</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;CL/cl.h&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But to compile on OS X, with the headers in <code>OpenCL.framework</code>, it would have to be</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;OpenCL/cl.h&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to specify that <code>CL/</code> should be an alias to <code>OpenCL/</code>, without modifying the source code?</p>